Reasoning: The paper focuses on learning vision-based manipulation skills for robotic grasping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method proposed in the paper uses deep reinforcement learning and leverages over 580k real-world grasp attempts, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of RGB vision-based perception also suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the ability of the method to respond dynamically to disturbances and perturbations, which suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
